# HANDOFF — <REPO_FRIENDLY_NAME>

Live cross-session resume point. Read at session start; refresh at
milestones and before context compaction. **Every session's changes
land here — do not stack stale state, collapse resolved items into
one-line entries.**

## Current state (<ISO_DATE>)

<One paragraph — what the repo is actively working on right now, who's
touching it, what's blocking. If empty, say so: "No active work; ready
for new intake.">

## Open threads

<Bulleted list of in-flight items that a resuming session must pick up.
Include: initiative/plan reference, blocker, next concrete action.>

- <e.g. "PLAN-XXX PR-YYY — awaiting review comments on X">
- <e.g. "Dependabot #NN — merge conflict; @dependabot rebase pending">

## Next-session start-here

<3-5 sentences telling the next session exactly where to look first.
Point at plans/PLAN files, HANDOFF sections, or DECISIONS entries by
