without reading the entire repo history.>

## Recent decisions

<Link, don't duplicate. Cite the DECISIONS.md entries touched in the
current or most recent milestone (last 1-2 weeks). Old entries stay
in DECISIONS.md; only pointers here.>

- <DECISION_ID> — <one-line summary> (`<DECISIONS_PATH>#<anchor>`)

---

**Maintenance protocol:**

- Update `Current state` on every commit that changes what the repo is
  doing.
- Move resolved `Open threads` to `Recent decisions` (with the
  DECISION-ID) or to git commit history.
- Prune `Recent decisions` — anything older than 4 weeks belongs only
  in `DECISIONS.md`.
- Never `git rm HANDOFF.md` — the file itself is the durable
  cross-session anchor; the content evolves.
